<section id="command-portmode">
    <title>PORTMODE</title>
<indexterm><primary>PORTMODE</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>PORTMODE</command> <parameter>modestring</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Sets the mode (speed, parity, data bits, and stop bits) of the open COM port.
The port characteristics (such as speed and flow control) cannot be set through MSWLogo.
</para>

<para>The <parameter>modestring</parameter> must be of the form <userinput>"COM<replaceable>n</replaceable>:<replaceable>SPEED</replaceable>,<replaceable>PARITY</replaceable>,<replaceable>DATA</replaceable>,<replaceable>STOP</replaceable></userinput>.
This is the format as the DOS MODE command.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
    <programlisting><userinput>PORTMODE "com1:9600,n,8,1
</userinput>
</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
